route.name: Outback on the Oodnadatta Track by Allison Piercy
route.description:
POIs at main campsites, free camping anywhere in between along the track. Make your own adventure! 
Do your research before relying on this for water sources and food options.

course_points.n: Turn left onto Oodnadatta Track, D95
Keep right onto Oodnadatta Track, D95
Turn right onto Kempe Road, D95
Turn left onto Stuart Highway, A87

point_of_interest.name: Marree hotel
point_of_interest.description: Free camp at the pub, Grocery store, pub meals, hot shower $ donation

point_of_interest.name: Algebuckina Bridge
point_of_interest.description: SAs longest bridge, nice campsite, permanent water hole if desperate (treat water)

point_of_interest.name: Coward Springs
point_of_interest.description: Water tanks, hot showers, paid camping, coffee cart with fresh date scones, natural hot spa

point_of_interest.name: Marla Roadhouse
point_of_interest.description: Paid campsite, Greyhound bus terminal, general store, pool, pub meals

point_of_interest.name: William Creek Campground
point_of_interest.description: Paid camp ground near the pub, hot showers, no groceries, free water tap outside pub

point_of_interest.name: Oodnadatta Pink Road House
point_of_interest.description: Paid campsite, water over the counter at cafe, paid water station may be out of service, great food, grocery store
